IBM Sued by SEC for Alleged Bribes of China, Korea Officials

-- B y   T o m   S c h o e n b e r g
-- 
2011-03-18T15:35:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/ibm-sued-by-sec-for-alleged-bribes-of-chinese-korean-government-officials.html
  International Business Machines
Corp. (IBM)  gave cash and gifts to officials in  China  and  South Korea 
from 1998 through 2009 in violation of the Foreign Corrupt
Practices Act, the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission
alleged today in a lawsuit filed in  Washington .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Schoenberg in Washington at 
 tschoenberg@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fred Strasser at 
 fstrasser@bloomberg.net  